Subprogram in PL/SQL

ğŸ”¹A subprogram in PL/SQL is a named block of code.
ğŸ”¹It is used to perform a specific task given by the user.
ğŸ”¹Instead of writing the same code again and again, we write it once as a subprogram and reuse it wherever needed.
ğŸ”¹This helps to keep the code clean, organized, and efficient.


âœ… Key Points:
ğŸ”¹Subprograms are named PL/SQL blocks.
ğŸ”¹They are stored in the database and can be called whenever needed.
ğŸ”¹Breaking the big programs into smaller programs .
ğŸ”¹It Can accept parameters and return output.

Types of Subprograms:

   1) Procedure ---Performs a task. May or may not return a value.
   2) Function ----Always returns a single value. Used in expressions.
